        "## Key Column Definitions\n",
        "\n",
        "Understanding the columns correctly is essential before interpreting any analysis. Several columns use terminology that can be misread without hotel operations context.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Booking Identity Columns\n",
        "\n",
        "| Column | Type | Business Meaning |\n",
        "|---|---|---|\n",
        "| `hotel` | Categorical | Hotel type: City Hotel or Resort Hotel |\n",
        "| `is_canceled` | Boolean | Whether the booking was canceled (True/False) |\n",
        "| `reservation_status` | Categorical | Final outcome: Check-Out, Canceled, or No-Show |\n",
        "| `reservation_status_date` | Date | Date the status was last updated |\n",
        "\n",
        "**Important distinction:** `is_canceled = True` includes both true cancellations (31,965) and No-Shows (895). These are operationally different events. A cancellation gives advance notice; a No-Show does not. All analysis in this project separates these where relevant.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Date and Timing Columns\n",
        "\n",
        "| Column | Type | Business Meaning |\n",
        "|---|---|---|\n",
        "| `lead_time` | Integer | Days between booking date and arrival date |\n",
        "| `arrival_date_year` | Integer | Year of arrival |\n",
        "| `arrival_date_month` | String | Month name of arrival |\n",
        "| `arrival_date_week_number` | Integer | ISO week number of arrival |\n",
        "| `arrival_date_day_of_month` | Integer | Day of month of arrival |\n",
        "\n",
        "**Lead time** is one of the most analytically powerful columns in this dataset. A booking made 180 days in advance carries fundamentally different cancellation risk than a booking made 2 days in advance. This column enables one of the project's strongest findings.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Stay Duration Columns\n",
        "\n",
        "| Column | Type | Business Meaning |\n",
        "|---|---|---|\n",
        "| `stays_in_weekend_nights` | Integer | Number of Saturday/Sunday nights |\n",
        "| `stays_in_week_nights` | Integer | Number of Monday–Friday nights |\n",
        "\n",
        "**Derived column created:** `number of nights` = `stays_in_weekend_nights` + `stays_in_week_nights`\n",
        "\n",
        "This derived column is used as the primary stay duration metric throughout the project.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Guest Composition Columns\n",
        "\n",
        "| Column | Type | Business Meaning |\n",
        "|---|---|---|\n",
        "| `adults` | Integer | Number of adults in the booking |\n",
        "| `children` | Integer | Number of children |\n",
        "| `babies` | Integer | Number of infants |\n",
        "\n",
        "**Derived column created:** `total_guests` = `adults` + `children` + `babies`\n",
        "\n",
        "Used for data quality validation — bookings with zero adults were removed as invalid.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Meal Plan Column\n",
        "\n",
        "| Column | Values | Business Meaning |\n",
        "|---|---|---|\n",
        "| `meal` | BB, HB, FB, SC | Meal package included in the booking |\n",
        "\n",
        "Mapped to full names during cleaning:\n",
        "- **BB (Bed & Breakfast):** Room plus breakfast — the dominant package at 78.5% of bookings\n",
        "- **HB (Half Board):** Breakfast and dinner included\n",
        "- **FB (Full Board):** All three meals included — rare in city hotels (0.05%)\n",
        "- **SC (Self Catering):** Room only, no meals — 13.3% of bookings\n",
        "\n",
        "The meal distribution confirms the city hotel profile: guests primarily want accommodation and breakfast, not full board packages typical of resort properties.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Market Segment vs Customer Type — A Critical Distinction\n",
        "\n",
        "These two columns are frequently confused. They describe different dimensions of the same booking.\n",
        "\n",
        "#### `market_segment` — How the booking was sourced\n",
        "\n",
        "| Segment | Meaning |\n",
        "|---|---|\n",
        "| Online TA | Booked through an online travel agency (Booking.com, Expedia, etc.) |\n",
        "| Offline TA/TO | Booked through a traditional travel agent or tour operator |\n",
        "| Direct | Booked directly with the hotel (phone, website, walk-in) |\n",
        "| Groups | Booking sourced through a group sales channel (event organizers, tour operators) |\n",
        "| Corporate | Booking made through a corporate account or company arrangement |\n",
        "| Aviation | Airline crew layover bookings |\n",
        "| Complementary | Complimentary rooms — staff, press, familiarization trips |\n",
        "\n",
        "#### `customer_type` — The nature of the booking contract\n",
        "\n",
        "| Type | Meaning |\n",
        "|---|---|\n",
        "| Transient | Standard individual booking with no special contract |\n",
        "| Transient-Party | Individual booking traveling as part of a group but booked separately |\n",
        "| Contract | Booking under a formal negotiated agreement |\n",
        "| Group | Formally contracted group booking with defined terms |\n",
        "\n",
        "**Why the distinction matters critically:**\n",
        "\n",
        "The project discovered that market segment \"Groups\" and customer type \"Group\" have only **4 bookings in common** out of 13,809 Groups market segment bookings (0.03% overlap). They measure almost entirely different populations.\n",
        "\n",
        "- Market segment \"Groups\" = sourced through group channels, predominantly Transient and Transient-Party customer types with no binding contracts → 69.5% cancellation rate\n",
        "- Customer type \"Group\" = formally contracted group agreements regardless of source channel → 10.2% cancellation rate\n",
        "\n",
        "Using \"Groups\" without specifying which column produces completely different — and contradictory — cancellation statistics. This was one of the most important analytical discoveries in the project.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Distribution Channel Column\n",
        "\n",
        "| Channel | Meaning |\n",
        "|---|---|\n",
        "| Travel Agent/Tour Operator (TA/TO) | Booking came through an agent or tour operator platform |\n",
        "| Direct | Guest booked directly with the hotel |\n",
        "| Corporate | Booking made through a corporate travel arrangement |\n",
        "| GDS | Global Distribution System — large corporate travel platforms (Amadeus, Sabre, Travelport) |\n",
        "\n",
        "**Note on GDS:** GDS bookings represent only 0.2% of this hotel's bookings, indicating limited connectivity to large corporate travel management platforms. This is common for smaller city hotels without dedicated GDS distribution strategies.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Pricing and Revenue Columns\n",
        "\n",
        "| Column | Type | Business Meaning |\n",
        "|---|---|---|\n",
        "| `adr` | Float | Average Daily Rate — room revenue divided by number of nights |\n",
        "| `booked revenu` | Float (derived) | Total booking value = ADR × number of nights |\n",
        "\n",
        "**Important limitation:** ADR represents the contracted booking rate, not the final invoiced amount. It does not include F&B, spa, parking, or ancillary revenue. All revenue figures in this project measure room revenue only. Total guest spend is higher than these figures suggest.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Behavioral Signal Columns\n",
        "\n",
        "These columns proved to be among the most analytically valuable in the project:\n",
        "\n",
        "| Column | Type | Business Meaning |\n",
        "|---|---|---|\n",
        "| `lead_time` | Integer | Days before arrival the booking was made |\n",
        "| `is_repeated_guest` | Boolean | Whether the guest has stayed at this hotel before |\n",
        "| `previous_cancellations` | Integer | Number of times this guest has previously canceled |\n",
        "| `previous_bookings_not_canceled` | Integer | Number of prior completed bookings |\n",
        "| `booking_changes` | Integer | Number of modifications made to this booking |\n",
        "| `total_of_special_requests` | Integer | Number of special requests made at booking |\n",
        "| `days_in_waiting_list` | Integer | Days the booking spent on a waiting list |\n",
        "\n",
        "These columns individually predict cancellation behavior with measurable and consistent patterns. Together they form the basis for a behavioral risk flagging system.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Deposit Type Column\n",
        "\n",
        "| Value | Meaning |\n",
        "|---|---|\n",
        "| No Deposit | No financial commitment required upfront |\n",
        "| Non Refund | Non-refundable rate — payment collected, not returned if canceled |\n",
        "| Refundable | Deposit collected but refundable upon cancellation |\n",
        "\n",
        "**Critical discovery:** In this dataset, 99.8% of Non Refund bookings are classified as canceled. This appears to contradict the expectation that non-refundable bookings cancel less. Investigation revealed that 97% of Non Refund bookings belong to Groups and Offline TA/TO market segments with an average lead time of 217 days. These are not individual guest non-refundable bookings — they are wholesale allotment contracts where blocks of rooms are pre-loaded into the system and released (recorded as \"canceled\") when unused. This is standard hotel operations, not guest behavior.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Implication for revenue analysis:** The €3,160,849 in Non Refund canceled revenue cannot be reliably classified as \"secured\" revenue. Whether these contracts required upfront payment cannot be determined from booking data alone. This requires accounting record verification."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "nTWeoDp7VZ94"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# 5. Data Cleaning and Preparation\n",
        "\n",
        "## Cleaning Philosophy\n",
        "\n",
        "Every cleaning decision in this project follows one rule: **remove or qualify records that would silently distort the business metrics we are trying to measure.** No records were removed without a documented business justification.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Step 1: Filter to City Hotel Only\n",
        "\n",
        "**Decision:** Remove all Resort Hotel bookings.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Justification:** The project context is a city/luxury urban hotel environment. Resort and city hotels have fundamentally different booking behaviors:\n",
        "- Resort guests book months in advance, stay 7+ nights, travel seasonally\n",
        "- City hotel guests book 2-7 days out, stay 2-3 nights, travel for business or short leisure\n",
        "\n",
        "Mixing both hotel types would distort every KPI in the project — ADR distributions, lead time patterns, cancellation rates, and segment behavior are all structurally different between the two.\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "1qur4d6aWzLE"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "#removing the Resort Hotel from data\n",
        "df = df[df['hotel'] != 'Resort Hotel']\n",
        "print(f\"\\nDataset after filtering: {len(df):,} rows\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "vBp04O3XXHwd",
        "outputId": "c1206899-a130-4927-93c1-75370df5fc99"
      },
      "execution_count": 49,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "\n",
            "Dataset after filtering: 79,330 rows\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
