        "**Interpretation:** The non-completion problem is overwhelmingly driven by advance cancellations. No-Shows, while operationally disruptive, represent only 1.2% of bookings. The important analytical distinction here is that cancellations and No-Shows require different responses. Cancellations can be addressed through deposit policies, stricter cancellation terms, and behavioral risk flagging — all of which depend on receiving advance notice. No-Shows by definition give no advance notice and must be addressed through overbooking policy calibration.\n",
