        "**Observation:** Realization rates vary from 31.4% for Groups to 93.2% for Complementary. Among commercial segments, Direct (78.1%) and Corporate (75.5%) perform above average, while Online TA (58.5%), Offline TA/TO (57.1%), and Groups (31.4%) all fall below.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Interpretation:** This chart makes visible what the ADR and occupancy report cannot show. A Groups booking and a Direct booking may look identical in a standard revenue report — same room, same rate. But on average, for every €1 booked from Groups, the hotel receives only 31 cents. For every €1 booked direct, the hotel receives 78 cents. The realization rate is the quality filter that standard metrics lack.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Business implication:** Revenue growth strategies focused on increasing booking volume from Groups or OTA channels are optimizing for the wrong metric. Volume increases in low-realization segments produce booked revenue that largely does not materialize.\n"
