      "source": [
        "## 8.3 The Lambda Verification\n",
        "\n",
        "During the Phase 3 revenue analysis, a technically risky calculation method was flagged and independently verified. The original segment-level realized revenue calculation used a groupby lambda that referenced an outer dataframe — a pattern that can produce incorrect results if the dataframe index has been reset.\n",
        "\n",
        "The calculation was re-run using a safer, more reliable method:"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "UDqckmTNhipu"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "completed_rev = df[df['completed'] == True].groupby(\n",
        "    'market_segment', observed=True)['booked revenu'].sum()\n",
        "\n",
        "total_rev = df.groupby(\n",
        "    'market_segment', observed=True)['booked revenu'].sum()\n",
        "\n",
        "segment_final = pd.DataFrame({\n",
        "    'booked': total_rev,\n",
        "    'realized': completed_rev\n",
        "}).fillna(0)"
      ],
